{
  "_comment": [
    "Flow Think MCP Server Configuration for Claude Code",
    "",
    "This file contains the MCP server configuration for flow-think,",
    "which provides structured thinking capabilities with step tracking,",
    "confidence scoring, and Beads integration.",
    "",
    "Installation:",
    "  1. Run: ./scripts/install.sh",
    "  2. Or manually add 'mcpServers' section to ~/.claude.json",
    "",
    "Configuration options (environment variables):",
    "  FLOW_MCP_OUTPUT_FORMAT: console|json|markdown (default: console)",
    "  FLOW_MCP_MAX_HISTORY: Maximum steps to retain (default: 100)",
    "  FLOW_MCP_SESSION_TIMEOUT: Session timeout in minutes (default: 60)",
    "  FLOW_MCP_BEADS_SYNC: Enable Beads integration (default: true)",
    "  FLOW_MCP_LOW_CONFIDENCE: Low confidence threshold (default: 0.5)",
    "",
    "See: tools/flow-think/README.md for full documentation"
  ],

  "mcpServers": {
    "flow-think": {
      "_comment": "Standalone executable (no runtime required)",
      "command": "~/.flow/mcp/flow-think/flow-think-mcp",
      "args": [],
      "env": {
        "FLOW_MCP_BEADS_SYNC": "true",
        "FLOW_MCP_OUTPUT_FORMAT": "console"
      }
    }
  }
}
